Some worry that Trump's bombastic speeches will drive important Hispanic voters away from Republican forces and hinder brand renewal.
However, according to ABC News and Washington Post poll results released Monday, six in 10 Republicans are on the same page as Trump on immigration issues.
As long as migration is in the spotlight, so is Donald Trump.
Dissatisfaction with the regime is at its peak.
Donald Trump and Ben Carson currently garner a combined total of about half of the Republican vote. The popularity is significantly boosted by the fact that both have come to run as outsiders.
