There was a guy in my own student dorm who thought an unlocked door meant he was welcome in.
He saw things.
Make friends by baking.
You start your studies appropriately when baking is in, so if you're baking brownies and knocking on someone's door, you don't seem like a 50s, slightly odd case of, "Welcome to the neighborhood, I baked you something small. Smile when I pry personalities from you."
