This, of course, requires you to have reasonable baker skills.
If you're serving hapless lumps of flour, sugar and fat, others will probably pretend to be asleep when you knock on the door.
Waffling on food is also a common misdemeanor in student housing.
Of course, taking another chicken is stealing, but can you pour a splash of someone else's milk into your tea?
Always check with the owner of the milk carton.
You're likely to get the go-ahead, even if the milk quote yurts the can owner.
I understand that it’s annoying when someone gives you something, but try to handle it as adultly as possible – unlike my college friend, who poured detergent into her milk as punishment for milk thieves.
The woman is now in jail.
Don't make noise when others are trying to sleep or cringe.
Not only because it's polite, but it's also worth remembering that for every other hole you dig...
In my own dorm, a girl asked the occupant of the next room to turn the music down, since it was 3 a.m., and she had an exam in the morning.
