Following the death of teenager Michael Brown from a white police bullet in 2014, the Black Lives Matter movement gained support nationwide. The movement seeks to end the discriminatory treatment of black people by lawmakers and authorities.
In February, singer Prince alluded to the movement when he introduced the album of the year nominees at the Grammys.
"Albums still matter," he noted.
"Just like books and dark-skinned lives, albums still matter."
